# Centralized Logging & Observability

## 1. Logging Pattern
- **Format:** `[TIMESTAMP] [CATEGORY] [LEVEL]: Message | Data`
- **Levels:** - `INFO`: General app flow (e.g., "App Started").
    - `DEBUG`: Verbose technical details (e.g., "Braze SDK Payload").
    - `WARN`: Non-breaking issues (e.g., "Image failed to load").
    - `ERROR`: Breaking failures (e.g., "API 500").
- **Categories:** `[UI]`, `[SDK]`, `[AUTH]`, `[STORAGE]`, `[SYSTEM]`.

## 2. Centralized Logger Class
- **Requirement:** All logs must pass through a singleton `AppLogger`.
- **Global Toggle:** Provide a `DEBUG_MODE` flag (fetched from `StorageManager`) to enable/disable verbose logging in production.

## 3. Integration with Log Viewers
- **Console Output:** Use CSS styling in `console.log` for better readability in browser dev tools.
- **External Export:** Implement a `getLogs()` method that returns a JSON array of the last 50 logs for export to support or a remote viewer.
- **Braze Integration:** Critical `ERROR` logs should be sent to Braze as a Custom Event: `App_Error` with the error message as a property.

## 4. Logger Blueprint (JS)
```javascript
const AppLogger = {
    logs: [],
    MAX_LOGS: 100,
    //DEBUG_MODE: window.location.hostname === 'localhost',

    log(level, category, message, data = null) {
        const timestamp = new Date().toISOString();
        const logEntry = { timestamp, level, category, message, data };
        
        this.logs.push(logEntry);
        if (this.logs.length > this.MAX_LOGS) this.logs.shift();

        //if (this.DEBUG_MODE || level === 'ERROR') {
            const color = this.getColor(level);
            console.log(
                `%c[${timestamp}] [${category}] [${level}]: ${message}`,
                `color: ${color}; font-weight: bold;`,
                data || ''
            );
        //}
    },

    getColor(level) {
        switch(level) {
            case 'ERROR': return '#ff4d4d';
            case 'WARN': return '#ffa500';
            case 'DEBUG': return '#7f8c8d';
            default: return '#2ecc71';
        }
    },

    info(cat, msg, data) { this.log('INFO', cat, msg, data); },
    debug(cat, msg, data) { this.log('DEBUG', cat, msg, data); },
    warn(cat, msg, data) { this.log('WARN', cat, msg, data); },
    error(cat, msg, data) { this.log('ERROR', cat, msg, data); }
};